org.spf4j.stackmonitor

Class THash

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.spf4j.stackmonitor.THash
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Externalizable, Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TObjectHash

    public abstract class THash
extends Object
implements Externalizable
    Base class for hashtables that use open addressing to resolve collisions. removed compaction element to reduce memory footprint. use case for this implementation does not have removes. Created: Wed Nov 28 21:11:16 2001
    Version:
    $Id: THash.java,v 1.1.2.4 2010/03/02 00:55:34 robeden Exp $
    Author:
    Eric D. Friedman, Rob Eden (auto-compaction), Jeff Randall, zfarkas
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Field Detail

      • DEFAULT_LOAD_FACTOR

        protected static final float DEFAULT_LOAD_FACTOR
        the load above which rehashing occurs.

      • DEFAULT_CAPACITY

        protected static final int DEFAULT_CAPACITY
        the default initial capacity for the hash table. This is one less than a prime value because one is added to it when searching for a prime capacity to account for the free slot required by open addressing. Thus, the real default capacity is 11.
        See Also:
